Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
write_ml_timing_path(25.10)                        write_ml_timing_path(25.10)

Name
       write_ml_timing_path  -  Writes  timing-related  data  for JedAI to csv
       files

Syntax
       write_ml_timing_path

       [-help]

       [-anchor_file <string>]

       [-begin_end_pair]

       [-chain_levels <int>]

        [-chain_path]

       [-each_endpoint]

       [-from <pin_list>]

       [-gen_anchor]

       [-hpin]

       [-io_only]

       [-max_paths <int>]

       [-max_slack <float>]

       [-nworst <int>]

       [-partitions <partition_list>]

       [-path_group <string>]

       [-per_partition]

       -prefix <string>

       [-retime {aocv ssta path_slew_propagation aocv_path_slew_propagation}]

       [-retime_mode {path exhaustive}]

       [-start_pathid <int>]

       [-to <pin_list>]

       [-verbose]

        [-views <view_list>]

       Writes timing-related data for JedAI to csv files. It includes data for
       individual timing paths. Timing path data can  be  computed  in  either
       graph-based  analysis  (GBA) or path-based analysis (PBA) fashion using
       the -retime option.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes the  type  and  default
              information for each write_ml_timing_path parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command

              man write_ml_timing_path.

       -anchor_file <string>
              Specifies the name of the anchor file to be used as input.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -begin_end_pair
              Reports all violations between unique source and target register
              pairs.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -chain_levels <int>
              Specifies the chain level if -chain_path is enabled.

              Data_type: int, optional

       -chain_path
              Gets chained paths.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -each_endpoint
              Specifies whether to dump at least one path for each end point.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -from <pin_list>
              Dumps data from the specified pin(s).

              Data_type: tcl_obj, optional

       -gen_anchor
              Generates the anchor file.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -hpin  Dumps hpin in timing points.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -io_only
              Specifies that only the io path should be dumped.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -max_paths <int>
              Specifies the max_paths for report_timing.

              Data_type: int, optional

       -max_slack <float>
              Specifies the max_slack for report_timing.

              Data_type: float, optional

       -nworst <int>
              Specifies the nworst for report_timing.

              Default: 100

              Data_type: int, optional

       -partitions <partition_list>
              Specifies a partition list if -per_partition is set.

              Data_type: tcl_obj, optional

       -path_group <string>
              Specifies the path_group for report_timing.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -per_partition
              Specifies that only paths through top level partitions should be
              dumped.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -prefix <string>
              Specifies the prefix for the output files.

              Data_type: string, required

       -retime {aocv ssta path_slew_propagation aocv_path_slew_propagation}
              Specifies  the method to be used for reanalysis of specified set
              of paths with report_timing.

              Data_type: enum, optional

       -retime_mode {path exhaustive}
              Passes the specified retime mode to report_timing. To understand
              the difference between the two retime modes,  path  and  exhaus-
              tive, see report_timing.

              Data_type: enum, optional

       -to <pin_list>
              Dumps data to the specified pin(s).

              Data_type: tcl_obj, optional

       -start_pathid <int>
              Specifies the starting path id.

              Default: 1

              Data_type: int, optional

       -verbose
              Displays a more detailed message.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -views <view_list>
              Dumps the timing path for the specified analysis view(s).

              Data_type: tcl_obj, optional

Example
              * The  following  command  writes  out  the attributes of timing
                paths to csv files with the specified prefix:

                write_ml_timing_path -prefix out/ -max_paths 10000 -nworst 1

Related Information
              * init_ml

              * report_timing

              * write_ml_design

              * write_ml_library

              * write_ml_timing_graph

